# pins.env -- version + checksum pins for the sandbox provisioning wrappers.
#
# This file is the ONLY moving part of the sandbox/ tree (see
# docs/design/PROVISION.DESIGN.md, "Sandbox wrapper tree"). All behavioral
# churn lives inside clai, behind these pins: rolling out new provisioning
# behavior to every provider = editing this file in ONE reviewed change
# (the pin bump is the review gate, per the supply-chain stance documented
# in .claude/hooks/session-start.sh and ai-tools issue #72).
#
# Sourced (and exported) by sandbox/provision.sh. Plain KEY="value"
# assignments only -- no logic, no command substitution.
#
# To bump the pin: set CLAI_VERSION to the released version (the release
# tag is clai-v${CLAI_VERSION}) and CLAI_SHA256 to the sha256 of that
# release's wheel asset (the GitHub release API reports it as the asset's
# digest). If either is ever reset to UNSET, provision.sh fails
# LOUDLY-but-open: it logs the fill-in procedure and exits 0 so sessions
# still start.

# clai wheel (executable code: pinned + checksum-verified, fail-closed
# per artifact -- a mismatch refuses to install). Session hook scripts
# ship INSIDE this wheel (installed by `clai hooks install`), so they
# roll out via the same CLAI_VERSION bump -- no separate hooks pin.
# Current pin: clai-v0.5.3 (2026-07-07), wheel clai-0.5.3-py3-none-any.whl,
# now released from template-tools (ai-tools consolidated in -- see #84).
CLAI_VERSION="0.5.3"
CLAI_SHA256="c4af48c0963cbdf400abc7de2f3b2f2f770468dca80d4e0b747f5664c1d120ae"

# Canonical source repos (stable; not pins). Skills and the MCP manifest
# are inert data and float to the latest default branch of
# TEMPLATE_TOOLS_REPO -- they are deliberately NOT pinned here.
# Post-#84 the clai wheel and ast-mcp release from template-tools too, so
# AI_TOOLS_REPO now points at the same repo (single owner -> one token
# covers the whole bootstrap). Kept as a distinct name for provision.sh's
# wheel-fetch call; retire the alias in a later cleanup.
TEMPLATE_TOOLS_REPO="nine-at-a-time-media/template-tools"
AI_TOOLS_REPO="nine-at-a-time-media/template-tools"
